'''Zaid Ismail Al-Dulaimi''' ({{langx|ar|زيد اسماعيل الدليمي}}; born 3 January 2002) is an Iraqi professional [[Midfielder (association football)|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder (association football)|defensive midfielder]] for Iraqi club [[Al-Talaba SC|Al-Talaba]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Zaid Ismail |url= https://www.besoccer.com/player/z-ismail-3418600 |publisher=BeSoccer |access-date=3 April 2026 |language=en}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Zaid first started getting regular playing time at local club [[Diyala SC|Diyala]] in the Iraqi second division, where he quickly became their most important player, leading them to a top-half finish in his final season at the club in 2022, before moving up to Iraq’s top tier with Kurdish club [[Newroz SC|Newroz]], where he also quickly established himself as a key player.<ref>{{cite web |title=لاعبي نوروز|url= https://www.aldaaenews.com/AR/Sport/Details/45635 |publisher=الداعي |access-date=3 April 2026 |language=ar}}</ref>

===Al-Talaba===
In January 2024, Iraqi giants [[Al-Talaba SC|Al-Talaba]] signed Ismail.

Zaid started the [[2025–26 Iraq Stars League|2025–26 Stars League]] season strongly, scoring against [[Zakho SC|Zakho]] in the opening game<ref>{{cite web |title=فوز للطلبة |url= https://shafaq.com/amp/ar/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%80%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D9%81%D9%88%D8%B2-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%A9-%D9%88%D9%86%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%AA%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%AD-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%86%D8%AC%D9%88%D9%85-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82 |publisher=Shafaq |access-date=3 April 2026 |language=ar}}</ref> and establishing himself as a key player for [[Al-Talaba SC|Al-Talaba]], playing 20 out of their opening 22 matches, while registering 4 goal involvements.<ref>{{cite web |title=زيد اسماعيل |url= https://www.winwin.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D8%A5%D8%B3%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%B2-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%AA-%D8%A3%D9%8A-%D8%B8%D8%B1%D9%81?amp |publisher=WinWin |access-date=3 April 2026 |language=ar}}</ref>

In early 2026, reports quickly started circulating all across Iraqi social
media pages and channels that [[Saudi Pro League]] side [[Al-Najma SC (Saudi Arabia)|Al-Najma]] were in talks to sign the midfielder, but no move materialised before the winter transfer window closed.

==International career==
===Iraq U-23===
Zaid received his first international call-ups in March and July 2023 with the [[Iraq national under-23 football team|Iraq U-23s]] during their preparations for the [[2024 AFC U-23 Asian Cup qualification|U-23 Asian Cup qualifiers]].<ref>{{cite web |title=ضمت  50 لاعباً |url= https://shafaq.com/amp/ar/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%80%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9/%D8%B6%D9%85%D8%AA-50-%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7-%D9%85%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84-%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%B6%D9%8A%D8%B1%D8%A7-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%B5%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9 |publisher=Shafaq |access-date=3 April 2026 |language=ar}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=مدرب منتخبنا |url= https://alrabiaa.tv/article/47571/%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%B1%D8%A8-%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D9%88%D9%84%D9%85%D8%A8%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%B9%D9%84%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%B7%D9%88%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%A9-48656 |publisher=AlRabiaa |access-date=3 April 2026 |language=ar}}</ref>

===Iraq===
Zaid broke into the [[Iraq national football team|Iraqi national team]] at the [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup]], where he made his debut and a further two appearances, putting down big performances and being a standout for Iraq during the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |title=زيد اسماعيل |url= https://www.winwin.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D8%A5%D8%B3%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%8A%D9%84-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%B2-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%AA-%D8%A3%D9%8A-%D8%B8%D8%B1%D9%81?amp |publisher=WinWin |access-date=3 April 2026 |language=ar}}</ref>

Following the Arab Cup, Ismail was called up to Iraq’s squad to face [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] in Mexico for a play-off match which would determine the final spot at the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]], where he went on to play as Iraq won the match to qualify for their first World Cup in 40 years.<ref>{{cite web |title=لاعب المنتخب الوطني |url= https://almaalomah.me/news/127461/sports/%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86%D8%AA%D8%AE%D8%A8-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%88%D8%B7%D9%86%D9%8A-%D9%8A%D8%A4%D9%83%D8%AF-%D8%AC%D8%A7%D9%87%D8%B2%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D9%84%D8%AD%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%8A |publisher=المعلومة |access-date=3 April 2026 |language=ar}}</ref>

